The paper discusses a motion planning paradigm for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bayesian updates also suggests a probabilistic approach, which is a common theme in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also mentions constraints and obstacles in the configuration space, which suggests a control systems perspective (cs.SY).
